postcontent: Nice condition Leupold Vari-X III 3.5-10x40mm Long Range 30mm with Mk4 M1 target knobs and upgraded mil-dot reticle. These scopes were the predecessors to the current Mark IV series. These were developed for the military as a cost-saving measure to the then current Ultra scopes. The lens and coatings were the same as the Mk4s and the Ultras but a wire MilDot reticle is used with the football shaped dots. The internals and tube thickness of the Ultra/Mk4s are said to be more robust but you'd have to work hard to break a Vari-X III Long Range. It carries Leupold's full lifetime warranty. location: Triad Area, Winston Salem, North Carolina
postcontent: Early Chinese milled SKS with blade bayonet. The rifle was manufactured in China's Jianshe Arsenal /26\, most likely in the last half of 1957, as it has a (2 million) series S/N on the receiver along with the /26\ symbol. Other markings on the receiver, are: "SKS 7.62 MADE IN CHINA" and "CJA SFLD.MI". Numbers match on all numbered metal parts. There's no markings on the wood.This is not your run-of-the-mill, stamped, light-weight barrel-lugged Chinese version, like a Norinco, but an early heavy-duty Chinese example having a milled receiver and trigger frame, as well as the heavy screwed-in type barrel and Russian style blade bayonet. The wood furniture and all metal parts are in excellent condition and the barrel bore is bright and shiny. The gas tube and piston were found to be in excellent condition, not dirty or corroded. Looks as if it was never shot at all.I purchased the rifle over 3 years ago from the person that originally purchased it after importation in the 90's. He said he removed the cosmoline as best as he could, shot a few rounds through it, then kept it in his safe all these years until he sold it to me. I purchased it because of its condition and the fact that I hadn't seen such a nice early milled Chinese for sale in a long time. I've never shot it myself, but did disassemble and inspect thoroughly, then gave it a good wipe-down and oiling and put it in my safe. I had planned to hold on to this one but I need the space in my safe. The cleaning kit in the buttstock and sling are included.We can meet in the Winston-Salem, Greensboro, High Point area. title: For Sale/Trade:  Colt LE6720 Custom AR15
postcontent: This is the latest AR15 that I've customized and I am now putting it up for sale to make room for my next project. I've invested a lot of time and money into this rifle and am very pleased with the final product; anyone who purchases this weapon system will not be disappointed. I will list the upgrades and the value of each to make it easier to discern the rifle's worth.-Colt Lightweight Billet Upper and Lower Receivers-Lightweight M4 Chrome Lined 16.1" Barrel (1:7 Twist)-Mil-Spec Buffer Tube/Magpul CTR 4 Position Telescoping Stock ($60)-Magpul MOE Grip W/ Storage Compartment ($30)-Magpul Enhanced Trigger Guard ($25)-Magpul MBUS Flip Up Sights ($35 ea.)-Vortex Strikefire II Red Dot/Green Dot Holographic Optic ($200)-Yankee Hill Machine Aluminum Alloy Quad Rail W/ End Cap ($150)-Yankee Hill Machine .625 Low Profile Gas Block W/ Carbine Length Gas Tube ($50)-5 Position Adjustable Forward Vertical Grip W/ Storage Compartment ($50)-Tactical 660 Lumen Flashlight W/ Wired Pressure Switch [Includes Strobe, SOS, and 5 Intensity Settings ($100)]-BCMGunfighter VLTOR Ambidextrious Charing Handle ($70)-2 Stage 5.5lb Trigger [This gives the trigger a crisp break before the chambered round is fired. ($85)]-Magpul XTM Rail Panels-Magpul M4 Generation 3, 30 round Window Magazines ($20 ea.)As you can see, I've customized this rifle to the highest degree. I used the lightweight design to build a tactical rifle that can be maneuvered and handled with ease. I've shot this rifle only for testing purposes and quality control and it has performed flawlessly at every corner. Along with all the attachments that I've added, I still of course have all of the orignal factory parts which were eventually replaced with ones that I felt were of an even more superior quality. Colt makes an amazing Bolt Carrier Group (BCG) but the Nickel Boron Supreme BCG is absolutely phenomenal. Nickel Boron is considered a self-lubricating metal, requires almost no oil, and can be run for much longer times and in harsher conditions. I did extensive research on the company and could not find another to match their standard. When fired, this rifle is of course, extremely loud, but outside of that it has the feel and response of a finely tailored machine. It's appearance is sleek and I could not be happier with how this system turned out. title: For Sale:  45 cal Glock,  model 36
postcontent: Model 36 Glock in "like new" condition,  see photo.  One magazne.   Glock 36 Specifications Caliber: .45 Auto Length: 177 mm / 6.96 in. Height: 121 mm / 4.76 in. Thickness: 28 mm / 1.10 in. Weight (unloaded): 635 g / 22.42 oz. Sight Radius: 150 mm / 5.91 in. Barrel Length: 96 mm / 3.77 in. Trigger Pull: ~2.5 kg / ~5.5 lbs. Magazine Capacity: standard 6 rounds + 1 in barrelAction:  Striker Fire, Dual Action Only   Glock 36 | G36  The GLOCK 36 packs 6 rounds of .45 Caliber AUTO stopping power in a package that fits the hands of most any user. The G36 is easily concealed, and incorporates a single stack magazine. The G36 measures only 1.13 in. in width which makes controlling recoil very simple. The G36 is easy-to-use, hard to see, and tough to face.   Glock calls the model 36 a Slimline™ pistol because it uses a single stack magazine resulting in a thin and flat package. The big advantage is that you do not sacrifice stopping power for increased concealability.The grip is textured on all surfaces and has a concave channel near the top on the left side which allows you to rest your thumb. The grip is thin and fits most hands well.  The gun has no sharp edges or rough spots and carries very well. The muzzle end of the slide is tapered to aid in quick and sure one-hand re-holstering, which is an important skill to practice along with drawing and assuming a firm firing position.supplies with the G36.  Like all Glocks, the G36 is a striker-fired DAO utilizing the Glock “Safe Action” design. When the slide is cycled, the firing pin is set in a half-cocked “safe” position, and is activated only by the trigger safety release toggle, which disengages the firing pin safety allowing the gun to fire. The safety being built integral with the trigger is especially good if you are in a situation where you are on the move or engaging multiple targets. As soon as your finger is off the trigger the gun is in a safe condition and a third safety interlock prevents the gun from discharging if it is dropped. While some have criticized the Glock’s trigger safety, as opposed to a manually set safety, it is a very deliberate design. The gun only fires if the trigger is fired. No other operation is required to take it from a safe to fire mode. It is also immediately obvious if the gun is cocked. The trigger remains in the rearmost position when not cocked and moves forward when the slide is cycled. It is also easy to see and feel if a round is chambered because the extractor projects out slightly from the slide when a cartridge is loaded. This is an important visual check, as the gun could be cocked and a round not chambered. Summary:The Glock 36 offers a high-quality, accurate and reliable alternative to a full-size service pistol, expecially when carrying a .45 under light clothing. Concealability is excellent with almost no loss in performance.  The Glock 36 allows carrying that .45 in really hot weather in comfort.

title: For Sale:  NIB SPRINGFIELD EMP4 9MM
postcontent: We have for sale NIB 1911 EMP® 4” Lightweight Champion™ 9mm.         For over 100 years, the 1911 pistol design has earned high praise for its near-perfect ergonomics, reliability, and effectiveness. Springfield Armory® engineered the original EMP® with an all-new patented short action. Seventeen re-designed parts later, the EMP® came out a smaller, more comfortable, and more concealable package optimized for the smaller 9MM and .40SW calibers. Among the community of those who know, it has earned a reputation as one of the most shootable compact pistols ever. The all-new 4″ Lightweight Champion™ offers a longer four-inch barrel that presents increased sight radius and more practical accuracy. Let’s not forget the extra velocity the longer barrel adds to any given cartridge. Better yet, the EMP® 4″ offers an extra half inch of height, providing plenty of room for a strong and positive grip. The EMP® 4″ is loaded with extras like a fiber optic front sight and two-dot, low-profile combat rear sight for effortless target acquisition. Ambidextrous safety levers, a match-grade barrel, and Posi-Lock™ grip texture to the front strap add extra high value benefits for the serious shooter. Not only is the new EMP® 4″ a controllable gun, it packs ten rounds (in 9mm) plus one more in the chamber. That’s in a slender single stack pistol, not a thicker double stack design. In fact, the new EMP® 4″ offers the same reduced grip circumference that made the original so successful. Looks aren’t everything, but the Cocobolo wood grips and two-tone forged stainless steel slide and black anodized aluminum (9MM) or Carbon Steel Black Armory Kote™ (.40SW) frame make the EMP® a looker sure to turn heads at the range. But you know it’s what’s under the covers that counts. While the EMP® 4″ might be the perfect carry gun, it’s new size makes it ideal for home defense, concealed carry or a little fun at the range.
